rComments: If you want a great mark, you should not enroll to this course. He divides the final mark into smaller %s: 3 gr. projects, mid-term, final, class contrib., group assess. and you end up with more than 50% weight of the final mark in the hands of others. Project guidelines were vague/incomplete. Class discussions can become irrelevant, long, boring.

His first year teaching with Woodsworth, have to say i was pleasently surprised by his passion and knowledge for the subject. Like's to get the class involved. Testing is fair; 2 tests worth 35% each. There is a fair amount of group work - 3 assignments. Overall, this course is great for anyone interested in learning about Strategic HR Management..
Teaches from the book with no new original or insightful thought
